WEBVTT

00:02:26.825 --> 00:02:33.224
he had conceived, theorized,
designed, passed and gotten ratified

00:02:33.248 --> 00:02:34.789
the US Constitution.

00:02:34.813 --> 00:02:37.050
And just to give you
some sense of the enormity

00:02:37.074 --> 00:02:39.146
of what that accomplishment actually was,

00:02:39.170 --> 00:02:42.065
although Madison
couldn't have known it at the time,

00:02:42.089 --> 00:02:47.400
today that same constitutional technology
that he invented is still in use

00:02:47.424 --> 00:02:49.105
not only in the US,

00:02:49.129 --> 00:02:50.613
but, 230 years later,

00:02:50.637 --> 00:02:52.980
in places like Canada,

00:02:53.004 --> 00:02:54.824
India,

00:02:54.848 --> 00:02:56.371
South Africa,

00:02:56.395 --> 00:02:57.993
Brazil.

00:02:58.017 --> 00:03:00.897
So in an extraordinary range
of contexts all over the world,